comments:
Abolished 1.4.1934 and divided between the parishes of Alton and 
    Croxden. See also Table 2, note (j).
Abolished 1.4.1934 and added to the parish of Waterhouses.

Renamed 1.4.1974 to become the parish of Caverswall & Werrington. 
    See also Table 2, notes (a), (f), (g), (m), (n) and (p).

That part until 1.4.1934 formed 1.4.1934 formed parts of the 
    parishes of Alton, Bradley in the Moor and Checkley. See also Table 2, note 
    (i).

Created 1894 from the part of the parish of Caverswall in Longton 
    Municipal Borough. Abolished 1.4.1896 and added to the parish of Longton. 
    See also Table 2, note (d).

Created 1.4.1896 out of the parish of Dilhorne. See also Table 
    2, notes (n) and (p).

That part until 1.4.1934 formed part of the parish of 
    Cheddleton. See also Table 2, note (i).

That part which until 1.4.1896 formed the parish of East Vale. 
    See also Table 2, note (d).
Created 1.10.1896 out of the parishes of Kingsley, Cheadle, Farley and Cotton. See also Table 2, note (p).

That part which until 1.10.1896 formed part of the parish of 
    Denstone. See also Table 2, note (e).

That part which until 1.4.1922 formed part of the parish of Caverswall. 
    See also Table 2, note (f).
Created 1.4.1934 out of the parishes of Waterfall, Cauldon, Calton and Ilam. See also Table 2, notes (h) and (p).
